value.title: Biden pushes back against critics, touts 'Cabinet of firsts'
value.excerpt: After weeks of pressure from all sides of the Democratic Party’s vast coalition over the makeup of his incoming administration, President-elect Joe Biden on Wednesday pushed back against his critics as he made another history-making Cabinet nomination.

value.title: Biden Cabinet pick Jennifer Granholm promoted 'pee tape,' Russian collusion claims
value.excerpt: Jennifer Granholm, President-elect Joe Biden's pick to be energy secretary, heavily promoted claims that President Trump's campaign colluded with Russia to win the 2016 election, even mentioning an unsubstantiated "pee tape."

value.title: Pompeo applauds Barr's loyalty to Trump following AG's resignation
value.excerpt: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo praised Attorney General William Barr and lauded his loyalty to President Trump just a day after Barr resigned from his post.

value.title: Biden's Treasury nominees meet with racial justice activists, 'defund the police' supporters
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden's nominees to run the Treasury Department --  Treasury Secretary-designee Janet Yellen and Deputy Treasury Secretary-designee Wally Adeyemo -- held their first joint meeting Monday with racial and economic justice activists.

value.title: Rep. Ayanna Pressley tells Gavin Newsom to appoint a Black woman to VP-elect Kamala Harris' Senate seat
value.excerpt: "We absolutely cannot go backwards," Pressley tweeted Tuesday. "With the election of @KamalaHarris to VP-elect, @CAgovernor must prioritize this leadership, perspective & representation in the vacated U.S. Senate seat & appoint a Black woman."

value.title: Trump campaign files lawsuit over New Mexico ballot drop boxes
value.excerpt: As New Mexico electors cast their votes on Monday, President Trump's campaign team filed a suit over the state's use of ballot drop boxes.

value.title: Putin congratulates Biden on election victory
Internet fact-checker at firm that works with Facebook reveals distrust of Trump WH
value.excerpt: Companies like Facebook work with groups licensed by individuals at the International Fact-Checking Network.

value.title: As border numbers increase, CBP chief says US faces 'full-blown crisis' if Trump-era policies end
value.excerpt: The Trump administration announced Monday that 70,000 migrants were apprehended at the southwest border in November, a 64 percent increase compared to 2019 -- and a sign of a possible surge that Trump officials say could become a full-blown crisis if recent policies are ended.

value.title: Jim Jordan: Georgians understand ‘freedom,’ Trump policies at stake in Senate elections
value.excerpt: Georgians “understand” what is at stake in the Peach State’s upcoming Senate runoff elections, Rep. Jim Jordan, R-Ohio, said on Monday.

value.title: VC Daily: Venture Firms Ready for Payday; NVCA Lobbies Biden With Letter; SoftBank Ends Year on High Note
value.excerpt: Last week, the National Venture Capital Association sent a letter to President-elect Joe Biden to get a lobbying head start.

value.title: Hunter Biden email shows $400G unreported income from Burisma, states he needs to 'amend' tax returns
value.excerpt: Hunter Biden did not report “approximately $400,000” in income he collected from his position on the board of Ukrainian natural gas firm Burisma Holdings when he joined in 2014, according to an attorney for his firm who noted that his tax returns needed to be amended, a new email obtained by Fox News

value.title: Intel officials who called Hunter Biden story Russian disinformation should face consequences: Domenech
value.excerpt: There should be consequences for former intelligence officials who called the Hunter Biden story Russian disinformation, Federalist publisher Ben Domenech said on Monday.

value.title: Former WH communications director Alyssa Farah says GA Senate runoffs will play role in Hunter Biden probe
value.excerpt: Former White House communications cirector Alyssa Farah asserted Sunday that the result of January's Georgia Senate runoff races would play a role in the future of a probe into Hunter Biden's business dealings.

value.title: Scalise not ready to accept Biden win: 'Let the legal process play out'
value.excerpt: House Minority Whip Steve Scalise, R-La., said he will continue supporting efforts challenging the election results even as the Electoral College is set to officially elect Joe Biden as the next president on Monday.

value.title: Trump tells 'Fox & Friends' election challenges 'not over' ahead of Electoral College vote
value.excerpt: President Trump vowed that he and his campaign “are going to continue to go forward” with their legal challenges against November’s election results, despite the Electoral College getting set to cast their votes on Monday.

value.title: Trump supporters, counterprotesters clash in Olympia, Wash.
value.excerpt: Protests are raging on for another weekend in Olympia, Wash. Trump supporters and members of the Proud Boys gathered at Washington's state Capitol, along with leftist counterprotesters. There was at least one street brawl between the groups.

value.title: Jordan claims Trump 'paid what he owed' in response to NY Times report
value.excerpt: One poll says nearly three in four registered voters plan to tune in to see President Trump face off against Democratic nominee Joe Biden tonight.  MACCALLUM: Fireworks are anticipated as theshowdown comes against a tense backdrop in thenation.

value.title: Hunter Biden requested keys for new 'office mates' Joe Biden, Chinese 'emissary' to CEFC chairman, emails show
value.excerpt: Hunter Biden requested in 2017 that keys be made for his new "office mates," listing his father, President-elect Joe Biden, Jill Biden and his uncle, Jim Biden, for space he planned to share with an "emissary" for a chairman of a Chinese energy company, according to an email obtained by Fox News.

value.title: Mike Pompeo, Mike Pence go to bat for imprisoned Hong Kong media tycoon Jimmy Lai
value.excerpt: Top US officials are speaking out against the arrest and imprisonment of Hong Kong media tycoon Jimmy Lai. The 73-year-old billionaire and pro democracy advocate was denied bail Saturday after

value.title: Fox News Poll: Most Republicans say President Trump was robbed
value.excerpt: Sixty-eight percent of Republicans believe the election was stolen from President Trump, according to the latest Fox News national survey of registered voters.

value.title: Black Lives Matter accuses Biden of ignoring them: 'It's demeaning to our hurt and trauma'
value.excerpt: Black Lives Matter accused President-elect Joe Biden of ignoring their request for a meeting and disregarding the Black voters that helped secure his White House victory.

value.title: Bobulinski tells Tucker Carlson that Joe Biden lied about son Hunter's business dealings
value.excerpt: Former Hunter Biden business partner Tony Bobulinski claimed now-President-elect Joe Biden lied about having no knowledge of his son's foreign business dealings.

value.title: MSNBC's Maddow: I've learned from Trump era not to blindly trust government officials
value.excerpt: Liberal MSNBC host Rachel Maddow said Wednesday she had learned from the Donald Trump era not to blindly trust the word of government officials, an interesting assertion given her reliance on intelligence leaks,

value.title: US-China tensions worsen with Hunter Biden, Eric Swalwell revelations: GOP lawmakers
value.excerpt: The clouds over Hunter Biden, whose business dealings in China were investigated by two GOP committee chairs in the Senate, and Rep. Eric Swalwell, D-Calif., raise fresh questions about how the United States will confront one of its top strategic foes in 2021 and beyond.

value.title: AG Barr knew about Hunter Biden probe for months: report
value.excerpt: Attorney General William Barr reportedly knew about investigations into Hunter Biden’s business and financial dealings for months, and worked to stop them being disclosed to the public during the election campaign.

value.title: Whitmer says Michigan GOP went ‘too far’ against anti-Trump state Democrat
value.excerpt: Michigan state Republicans went “too far” in saying they would pull committee assignments from a state Democrat who threatened Trump supporters in a viral video, the state’s Democratic governor said Thursday.

value.title: Biden's pick of Denis McDonough for VA sparks pushback from veterans
value.excerpt: The aftermath of President-elect Joe Biden’s pick for secretary of Veteran Affairs has been met with responses of “surprise” after long-time Obama aide Denis McDonough was selected to be only the second non-veteran to take up the seat Thursday.

value.title: Pence says Trump ‘deserves his day’ in Supreme Court
value.excerpt: Saying “God bless Texas,” Vice President Mike Pence on Thursday gave a rousing endorsement of a lawsuit filed by the Texas attorney general and backed by President Trump that aims to throw out the election results in four key battleground states won last month by President-elect Donald Trump.

value.title: Kamala Harris’s husband will teach at Georgetown Law school
value.excerpt: Vice President-elect Kamala Harris’ husband Douglas Emhoff will join the staff of Georgetown University’s law school next month. Emhoff, 56, will be the first non-female and first Jewish ...
